-- Bank of England Court of Directors Head Sought by U.K.
-- B y   J e n n i f e r   R y a n
-- 2013-10-02T08:02:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-02/bank-of-england-court-of-directors-head-sought-by-u-k-.html
Cabinet Office has  advertised  for
candidates to replace David Lees, non-executive chairman of
Court of Directors of the  Bank of England .
*Role pays 48,000 pounds ($78,000) for an average two days per
week, and closing date for applications is Oct. 25 with
interviews in November, Cabinet Office says in statement
*NOTE: Court is central bank’s governing body. Lees was
initially going to stand down from post at the end of year after
overseeing bank’s absorption of new regulatory powers in April.
In July  he agree d to stay until end of June 2014, to provide
continuity during Mark Carney’s first year as governor
*NOTE: Court manages bank’s objectives and strategy, though not
formulation of monetary policy  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer Ryan in London at 
